$interpreted: Izumi: Ya-ho, fellas~ Nice weather we got today~
Guard: Stop right there. The area ahead is a restricted. Random people aren't allowed inside. Where is your special permit? Show me!

Izumi: Permit? I don't have that sort of thingy~
I've never heard about there being a restricted area here...
Guard: This is an emergency measure to address traitor Angelia. We need to prevent Sunshine Infantry from infiltrating the capitol.
Izumi: Oh boy~ That's quite troublesome...
Guard: If you don't have a permit, turn away and leave now!
Izumi: But I have to go to Atlas no matter what~
Guard: W, what do you want to do?
Izumi: Well, what else but...
Relief Soldier: Good work on the shift...
Relief Soldier: ... Eh, what's going on?

Izumi: Originally thought there would only be two people.
This will create too much of ruckus... Cleaning up will be a pain.
Izumi: Whatever, I'll figure out another way.
Guard: What did you say?
Izumi: I said that you guys are lucky~ I'll take my leave first.
Merchant: Miss, these are cosmetics from outside of the kingdom. Come check them out!
Izumi: Ooh~ The color of this nail polish is so cute!
Vendor: ... Right now, the roads between the capitol and Atlas are all locked down. Buying traveling products like these are pointless anyway...
Ralph: No need to worry. I have a special permit for traveling~
Izumi: (What matters is the permit itself, not the person who holds it, right~)
Izumi: Hmm, no annoying group of people tagging behind you. That makes things much easier for me.
Ralph: Who are you?
Izumi: Someone here to rob you. Brother~ behave yourself and get robbed by me~
Ralph: You little... why did you assault me all of a sudden...
Izumi: Hey, it's not sudden at all~ I said that I'm here to rob you~
Izumi: Found it, the permit~
Ralph: Damnit, give it back!

Izumi: Stay here and lick your wounds, brother.
Even though it hurts, you should survive, I think. Take care~
